    <!-- BLOCK 04: LANGUAGE FOCUS -->
    <section class="block" id="focus"><header class="block-head"><div class="block-num">04</div><div class="block-title-wrap"><div class="block-kicker">Language Focus</div><h2 class="block-title">My / Your / His / Her</h2></div><div class="block-time">≈ 8 min</div></header><div class="grammar-table-wrap"><table class="grammar-table"><thead><tr><th>Subject</th><th>Possessive adjective</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>I</td><td>my</td><td class="sample">This is my bag. / This is my laptop.</td></tr><tr><td>you</td><td>your</td><td class="sample">Is this your notebook? / Is this your charger?</td></tr><tr><td>he / Alex</td><td>his</td><td class="sample">It is his desk. / It is his coffee mug.</td></tr><tr><td>she / Mia</td><td>her</td><td class="sample">It is her pencil. / It is her notebook.</td></tr><tr><td>we</td><td>our</td><td class="sample">These are our books. / This is our workspace.</td></tr><tr><td>they</td><td>their</td><td class="sample">These are their toys. / These are their keys.</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class="grammar-rule"><strong>Rule:</strong> Use my, your, his, her, our, their before a noun to show ownership. Example: my bag, your book, his desk, her laptop, our classroom, their keys.</div><div class="error-card"><h3>Typical mistake</h3><p><span class="bad">Wrong:</span> This is I bag. / It is he laptop. / It is she phone.<br><span class="good">Right:</span> This is my bag. / It is his laptop. / It is her phone.</p></div><div class="block-nav"><a class="btn primary" href="#guided">Next: guided practice</a></div></section>

